The paper deals with graphical model selection, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics. The paper also discusses the sample complexity of this problem, which is related to the amount of data required for accurate model selection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also discusses the use of Gaussian random processes, which is a common tool in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and signal processing (cs.SI), making these sub-categories also likely.
